article.headline: TCU 73, Tulane 62
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Corey Santee scored 23 points and became TCU's all-time assist leader in a 73-62 win over Tulane on Wednesday night. Santee was 8-of-13 from the field. He got his 515th career assist at 5:50 of the second half, passing Prince Fowler for the school record. He finished with five on the night and a total of 516. Aaron Curtis added 13 points and Marcus Shropshire scored 12 for the Horned Frogs (11-5, 1-1 Conference USA). Nile Murry had 10 points for TCU, which trailed 32-31 at halftime. Marcus Kinzer scored 20 points on 8-of-18 shooting to lead the Green Wave (7-7, 0-3). Quincy Davis scored 13 points. Both teams shot below 40 percent for the game.
